{"lemma":"أَلْبِسَة","slug":"أَلْبِسَة","root":"ل.ب.س","root_slug":"ل-ب-س","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-ب-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لِباس","root":"لبس","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n37512","n37516"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clothes, raiment, vestment, dress"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/li.baːs/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n37512","headword_ar":"لِبَاسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clothing; dress; apparel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is worn;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libosN","text_ar":"لِبْسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malobasN","text_ar":"مَلْبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"milobasN","text_ar":"مِلْبَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuwsN","text_ar":"لَبُوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) or the last signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garments,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pieces of cloth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) the pl. of the first is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lubusN","text_ar":"لُبُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malobasN","text_ar":"مَلْبَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malaAbisu","text_ar":"مَلَابِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labAsu AlkaEobapi","text_ar":"لَباسُ الكَعْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhawodaji","text_ar":"الهَوْدَجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkaEobapi","text_ar":"الكَعْبَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libosu","text_ar":"لِبْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhawodaji","text_ar":"الهَوْدَجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clothing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering of pieces of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Kaabeh, and of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"camel-litter called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hwdj","text_ar":"هودج"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, Msb, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAsu Alt~aqowaY","text_ar":"لِبَاسُ التَّقْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [vii. 25,] (TA,) [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The apparel of piety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarse, and rough, and short, apparel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the covering of that portion of the person which modesty forbids one to expose;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) at which the preceding words of the verse glance; indicating that this is the main purpose of clothing; the additional purpose being to beautify and adorn one's self, and to repel heat and cold: (TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honest shame,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the shrinking of the soul from foul conduct, through fear of blame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayaA='u","text_ar":"الحَيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, K:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"faith."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Es-Suddee, K.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ibosu","text_ar":"اللِّبْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) written by Sgh ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ubosu","text_ar":"اللُّبْسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libosu AlEaZomi","text_ar":"لِبْسُ العَظْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~imoHaAqu","text_ar":"السِّمْحَاقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The pericranium"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, K:) to which is added, in some of the copies of the K, in the handwriting of the author, i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing pellicle that is between the skin and the flesh."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"covering"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (M.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAsu Aln~awori","text_ar":"لِبَاسُ النَّوْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The outer coverings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calyxes, of flowers."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) It is said in the Kur [lxxviii. 10,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajaEalonaA A@lol~ayola libaAsFA","text_ar":"وَجَعَلْنَا ا@لْلَّيْلَ لِبَاسًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we have made the night to be a covering"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: i. e., it covers, veils, or conceals, you by its darkness. (TA.) ―         -b3-  A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wife;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * K; *) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_izaArN","text_ar":"اـِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and a woman's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, * K: *) occurring in the Kur ii. 183: (S, M:) or there meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like a garment:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA:) because each embraces the other: or because each goes to the other for rest, and consorts with ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yulaAbisu","text_ar":"يُلَابِسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":") the other: (Zj, M, Bd, * TA:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmulaAbasapu","text_ar":"المُلَابَسَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ the mixing one's self and congregating, ” or “ the being mixed and congregated: ” (Ibn-'Arafeh, TA:) or because each conceals the state of the other, and prevents the other from acting viciously. (Bd.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"libaAsu AljuwEi","text_ar":"لِبَاسُ الجُوعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The utmost degree of hunger;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) when people are so hungry that they eat camels' fur with blood: (TA:) so termed because all-involving. (K.) It is said in the Kur [xvi. 113,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^a*aAqahaA A@ll~`ha libaAsa A@lojuwEi waA@loxawofi","text_ar":"فَاَذَاقَهَا ا@للّٰهَ لِبَاسَ ا@لْجُوعِ وَا@لْخَوْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So God made her to taste the utmost degree of hunger and of fear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, * TA. [See also 4 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*wq","text_ar":"ذوق"},{"kind":"text","text":".])"}],"source_refs":["K","M","Msb","S","A","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n37516","headword_ar":"لَبَّاسٌ","root":"lbs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having many clothes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuwsN","text_ar":"لَبُوسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who wears much clothing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru All~ubosi","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ اللُّبْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (so in the K accord. to the TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who confuses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confounds, much;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru All~abosi","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ اللَّبْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (so in a copy of the K [and this signification seems to be implied by what immediately precedes, and by what follows,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN lab~aAsN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ لَبَّاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the S: in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~abosi","text_ar":"اللَّبْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is evidently a mistake:]) you should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mulab~isN","text_ar":"مُلَبِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) for this is vulgar. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","TA"]}]}}